{
  "texts": [
    "However, it requires an effortful and consistent application to effect a notable change in prescribing behavior.",
    "There is variation in reported efficacy of education-based interventions in the literature [3,4,21,32,33].",
    "We found a good effectiveness of E&G-based interventions with low persistence of effect over time if the intervention is not reenforced (Table 1).",
    "These observations are consistent with those of a systematic review [30] on interventions conducted among primary care physicians.",
    "Possible solutions include continuous training for rotating staff (e.g., residents) and displaying costs of laboratory tests [4,11,32,104]."
  ]
}